parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the tire can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. In addition, the tire blowout can cause damage to the vehicle and its components, as well as spill cargo on the highway, creating a hazardous situation for other drivers.
symptoms: The tire suddenly explodes or blows out
causing the vehicle to lose control
or overturn. The tire may split its steel belts crosswise
and the ambient temperature may be high at the time of the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways or busy roads.
symptoms: The engine quits or shuts off while driving
the vehicle loses power and comes to a sudden stop
